&lt;p&gt;The solution with factory.setConfigurationFileName(configURL.getFile()); will&lt;br/&gt;
not work in all cases, especially if the configuration file is located in a jar.&lt;br/&gt;
Oli&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405632" author="timreilly@spherion.com" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2003 02:51:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Oli,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed the setConfigurationURL method last night. The patch implements this &lt;br/&gt;
change; as you describe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-factory.setConfigurationFileName(configURL.toString());&lt;br/&gt;
+factory.setConfigurationURL(configURL);&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
